{
  "description": {
    "title": "D3-6 flagship: the steel<->carbon joint cycle + the anti-leakage levers (CBAM cap-preserving vs OBA cap-relaxing)",
    "why_a_cycle_is_born": "Two identical steel producers (gamma=5, delta=2, sigma=5, beta=10, a_max=5) live in TWO markets at once: a steel product market (Sigma q + M = D, linear demand A_d=40 b_d=0.3, carbon-free elastic imports m=0.2 sigma_foreign=5) and a carbon market (Sigma e = Cap = 40). Because beta is FINITE, each firm abates a*=P_c/beta AND sheds output q=Cap/(sigma - P_c/beta), so at a FIXED cap the output q VARIES with the carbon price -- that endogenous q is exactly what closes the steel<->carbon loop into a genuine 2-way SCC (loop gain g = s_c*s_s = 0.627 in (0,1)). The unchanged damped Gauss-Seidel joint engine solves it.",
    "base_anchor": "Hand-verified finite-beta fixed point: P_steel*=60, P_carbon*=10, per-firm q*=5 (agg 10), a*=1, residual Sigma e* = (sigma-a*)q* = 40 = Cap, imports M*=12, demand D=22, leakage L=0.353 (vs the no-policy P_c=0 counterfactual P_s0=30, e0=125, M0=6). Joint Converged=1.",
    "integrity_contrast": "CBAM is cap-PRESERVING, OBA is cap-RELAXING. Under CBAM (border charge c*P_c*sigma_foreign folded INTO steel clearing, coverage c=0.5) leakage falls hard 0.353 -> 0.111 while gross emissions stay Sigma e = Cap = 40 (no free allowances issued). Under output-based allocation (phi=1 tCO2/t-steel) leakage barely moves 0.353 -> 0.326 AND OBA issues phi*Sigma q free allowances ON TOP of the cap, so Sigma e = Cap + phi*Sigma q = 40 + 13.33 = 53.33 -- gross emissions float up +33%. CBAM cuts leakage more while holding the cap; OBA buys weaker leakage protection by relaxing the cap. (The ranking is calibration-dependent; the cap-preserving-vs-relaxing structural fact is general -- V-D3-5 ruling #4.)",
    "investment_margin": "A cleaner H2-DRI option (sigma'=3) with trigger_mode='break_even' (M=1 so the reported trigger P* = M*theta = theta = 9). At the base P_c*=10 >= 9 the switch fires: sigma drops 5 -> 3, the cap loosens, P_c falls below the no-adopt anchor (ex-post regret permitted) and domestic output RECOVERS. Headline leakage uses the UN-ADOPTED sigma counterfactual (ruling #2), so it scores the WHOLE-policy effect including the induced tech-switch.",
    "rulings_exercised": "V-D3-5 #1 (theta/M kept separate; P* = M*theta reported as 'Clean Tech Trigger Price'), #2 (leakage counterfactual at un-adopted sigma; 'Conditional Leakage' the post-adoption-sigma' secondary), #3 (convergence-time leg-agreement assertion on the two producer faces), #4 (Sigma e = Cap + phi*Sigma q surfaced via 'Gross Emissions' + 'OBA Free Allocation')."
  },
